{
  "doc_id": "34456",
  "text": "This study was part of ongoing research at the ART service in Gugulethu township, Cape Town, which has previously been well described. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] Patients enrolled consecutively into the ART program from September 2002 were eligible for the study. Blood CD4 cell counts and plasma viral load (VL) levels were measured routinely pretreatment, every 4 months during ART, and when clinically indicated. VL assays were measured using the Versant HIV-1 RNA 3.0 assay performed on a 340 bDNA analyzer (Bayer Diagnostics, Tarrytown, NY) with a lower limit of detection of 50 RNA copies per milliliter.",
